    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-22T05:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-22T05:41:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Netherlands/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-22T12:00:00+01:19"
                            >May 22, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 22—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Department’s rush telegram No. 9, May 21, noon. Following information has
                    been obtained from the Foreign Office: <pb facs="0519" n="439" xml:id="pg_439"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Draft of proposed legislation has been in the Ministry of
                            Justice.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Draft must be approved by Chief of Division in the Ministry, Minister
                            of Justice, by the Cabinet and by the Council of State before
                            introduction into the second Chamber. Foreign Office stated “It may take
                            about 6 weeks to complete these steps in the case of legislation
                            regarding which there is no hurry”.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Foreign Office has no objection to our notifying Belgian Government
                            that such legislation is contemplated.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Emmet</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
